# Implementation Plan - Mascot Interactive Props & Scenario Mimicking

This plan details the design and implementation approach for adding interactive "props" (headphones, floating screens, controllers, etc.) and programming the companion mascot "Vedika" to detect the user's active window/scenario and dynamically react to it with matching animations and accessories.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Active Window Detection Strategy on Windows**
> To determine if the user is coding, gaming, watching YouTube, etc., we need to inspect the foreground application's process name and window title.
> We propose executing a fast, lightweight **PowerShell script** from the Electron main process via `child_process.exec` every 2 seconds.
> - **Why**: This runs instantly on Windows, has zero dependency compilation requirements (which avoids the high failure rate of native node modules like `active-win` on some setups), and securely provides the foreground window title and executable name.
> - If you move to macOS/Linux in the future, we would adapt the shell script to query `osascript` or `xdotool`.

