## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **1. Manual Scenario Override / Testing Interface**
> Do you want a way to manually force a specific scenario (e.g. force "gaming" or "music" mode) for testing or customization?
> We propose adding a **"Mimic Scenario Override"** section to the System Tray context menu so you can easily toggle and see each animation/prop even if you don't have the corresponding application open.
> 
> **2. Gaze Behavior during Mimicking**
> When a prop is active (like the code hologram panel or a reading tablet), should Vedika's eyes look at the prop instead of tracking the mouse cursor?
> We propose:
> - **Surfing Web / Reading PDF**: Eyes scan back and forth across the hologram screen.
> - **Coding / Office**: Eyes look slightly down towards the panel/clipboard, occasionally looking up at the cursor.
> - **Music / YouTube**: Eyes continue to track the user's cursor normally.

