## Proposed Changes

We will introduce the scenario detection in the main process, bridge the active scenario state via IPC to the renderer, and update the SVG, rig, and behavior planner layers to display and animate the props.

### 1. Main Process (Scenario Observer)

#### [MODIFY] [main.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Trail-V1/src/main.ts)
- Add a periodic query (every 2 seconds) using PowerShell to check the foreground window's title and process name.
- Map the title/process to one of the 7 target scenarios:
  - **Coding**: VS Code, Visual Studio, IntelliJ, etc.
  - **YouTube**: Browsers with "YouTube" in the window title.
  - **Web Surfing**: Browsers without "YouTube" in the title.
  - **Office**: Word, PowerPoint, Excel, etc.
  - **Gaming**: Full-screen games, steam, epic launcher, or common game titles.
  - **Reading PDF**: Window title containing ".pdf" or Adobe Reader.
  - **Music**: Spotify, iTunes, or YouTube Music titles.
- Send the detected scenario to the renderer via IPC (`active-scenario-changed`).
- Add a "Scenario Override" sub-menu in the System Tray for testing.

### 2. Preload & IPC Bridge

#### [MODIFY] [preload.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Trail-V1/src/preload.ts)
- Expose the IPC listener `onActiveScenarioChanged` so the renderer can receive state updates.

### 3. SVG Props Layer

