### 4. Rigging & Animation Logic

#### [MODIFY] [rig.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Trail-V1/src/renderer/rig.ts)
- Add support for changing base poses depending on the active scenario (e.g. moving/rotating arms to hold a controller, type on a keyboard, or hold a clipboard).
- Add support for showing/hiding prop SVG elements based on the scenario name.

#### [MODIFY] [behavior.ts](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Trail-V1/src/renderer/behavior.ts)
- Integrate the scenario state into the tick loop.
- Apply dynamic micro-animations for each state:
  - **Coding**: Alternate typing bob offsets on left/right arms (`Math.sin` driven).
  - **Music**: Rhythmic bobbing on head/torso.
  - **Gaming**: Fast controller-tapping arm vibrations.
  - **Reading/Surfing**: Scan gaze coordinate parameters left-to-right.

